Provides classes that run common measurement protocols on the
QuantumMachine OPX + Octave, and standalone scripts for specific tasks.

- `qmtools` Collection of QM protocols.
- `qmpipeline` Script using protocols for automated qubit characterization.
- `vgatepipeline` Easier loading and treating fo qmpipeline output.
- `vgatepipelineplotter` Jupyter widget to look at qmpipeline data.
- `pipeline_fits` Fit output data from various QM protocols.

See the doc strings, especially module doc strings, for further documentation.

# How to use
## Requirements and conda env
This implementation is for use with a single OPX1 and one Octave.
The current implementation is for qm-qua version 1.2.6.

qm-qua requires a specific Python version (3.12 for qm-qua 1.2.6)
The qm-qua package is only distributed via pip, not conda.
To prepare a conda environment use

    conda create -n qm -c conda-forge python=3.12
    conda activate qm
    pip install qm-qua==1.2.6 qualang-tools
    conda install -c conda-forge numpy scipy matplotlib

The pipeline and standalone scripts depend on further packages,
in particular the instruments package from https://github.com/QCMX/instruments
and

    conda install -c conda-forge qcodes pyvisa pyvisa-py

